Double Helix

double_helix(num_nodes=1000, noise=0, num_spirals=2)

{% endraw %} {% raw %}
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
from FRED.datasets import plot_directed_3d
X, flows, labels = double_helix()
plot_directed_3d(X, flows, labels, plot_minimal=False)
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
from FRED.datasets import plot_3d
plot_3d(X, labels, lim=12, use_plotly=True)
{% endraw %}

Note that the flows on each strand go opposite directions. When there's a sufficient amount of noise, the dataset looks like a big cylinder. Only the flows can unweave the strands.

{% raw %} 
X, flows, labels = double_helix(num_nodes=2000,noise=0.5, num_spirals=4)
plot_directed_3d(X, flows, labels, plot_minimal=True)
{% endraw %}
